# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We will track the trust gained by each person and if any person has gained a trust of n-1 people, and trusts nobody, he is our judge.

Since we have to store something i.e the trust we can use either a hashmap or a count array. but its better and efficient to use a count array when we know the range.
eg [0,0,2] indicates that the trust of person 3 is 2 and the other is 0.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Iterate over the trust array and 
Increase the count of trusted person ie A[i][1]++
Decrease the count of trusting person ie A[i][0]--
why, since the trust is unique, this person can never have value = n-1

Check the count array if n-1 exists and that is ans.

