**Consider a graph**
#There is an edge from person1->person2, if person1 trusts person2

**Town Judge Criteria**
**1. Town Judge trusts nobody**
There is no outgoing edge from town judge

**2. Everybody (except town judge) trusts town judge**
If there are "N" people(including town judge), then "N-1" people will trust town judge
Thus there will be exactly "N-1" incoming edges into town judge


```
class Solution {
public:
    int findJudge(int n, vector<vector<int>>& trust) 
    {
        vector<int>inDegree(n + 1, 0);
        vector<int>outDegree(n + 1, 0);
        for (vector<int>&currTrust : trust)
        {
            int trustedPerson = currTrust[1];
            int trustingPerson = currTrust[0];
            inDegree[trustedPerson]++;
            outDegree[trustingPerson]++;
        }
        //============================================================
        for (int person = 1; person <= n; person++)
        {
            if ((inDegree[person] == (n - 1)) && (outDegree[person] == 0))
                return person;
        }
        //===============================================================
        return -1;

    }
};
```

