# Please Upvote 😇
---
![image.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/de9459ba-f843-49b1-aa69-dcbce8ec4e67_1674463766.6991827.png)
We will use a hashmap to count the number of trust each person has got.
- If a person is trusted by someone, we will increase his trust count.
- If a person trusts someone, we will decrease his trust count.

Because the the judge will always get trusted and never trust himself.

``` java []
class Solution {
    public int findJudge(int n, int[][] trust) {
        // map to store the trust counts
        Map<Integer, Integer> adj = new HashMap<>();
        for (int[] e : trust) {
            // [a, b]
            // a trusts b, decrease a's count coz he'll never be the judge
            // b is trusted by a, increase b's count 
            adj.put(e[1], 1 + adj.getOrDefault(e[1], 0)); 
            adj.put(e[0], adj.getOrDefault(e[0], 0) - 1);
        }

        // now we will check from 1 to n, who has got n-1 trusts
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            if (adj.getOrDefault(i, 0) == n - 1) {
                return i;
            }
        }

        // if no one got n-1 trusts, there is no judge
        return -1;
    }
}

// TC: O(n), SC: O(n)
```
---
#### We can implement the same logic using an array instead of a hashmap *(Better runtime)*:
``` java []
class Solution {
    public int findJudge(int n, int[][] trust) {
        // each index is the each person, 
        // the value at every index is each of their trust counts
        // persons are from 1-n so we took a size of n+1 (0-based indexing)
        int[] adj = new int[n + 1]; 
        for (int[] e : trust) {
            // [a, b], a trusts b, b is trusted by a
            adj[e[0]]--;    // decrease a's count
            adj[e[1]]++;    // increase b's count
        }

        // now we will check from 1 to n, who has got n-1 trusts
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            if (adj[i] == n - 1) {
                return i;
            }
        }

        // if no one got n-1 trusts, there is no judge
        return -1;
    }
}

// TC: O(n), SC: O(n)
```

