solutions.content:
We use `vector<int> people` to all trust from other people.
If somebody trust to `people[i]` we increment by 1.

If `people[i]` trusts somebody, we can do anything that prevent `people[i]` get `N - 1` votes:
I do decrement, but we can also set to `-N` or `-1`, does't matter. Just make sure it prevents `people[i]` to get `N-1` trust from others.

The judge is the `people[i] == N - 1`;

Oh, I also allocate `people` size `N + 1`, so I can use indexes `[1..N]` instead of `[0..N-1]`, one extra element but less calculations.

```
class Solution {
public:
    int findJudge(int N, vector<vector<int>>& trust) {
        vector<int> people(N + 1, 0);
        for (vector<int> t: trust) {
            people[t[0]]--;
            people[t[1]]++;
        }
        for (int i = 1; i <= N; i++)
            if (people[i] == N - 1) return i;
        return -1;
    }
};
```

