# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
- Instead of adjacency list, we make array of indegrees and outdegrees for each person. We just the number of people that trust, not a record of it

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int findJudge(int n, int[][] trust) {
        int[] indegrees = new int[n+1];
        int[] outdegrees = new int[n+1];

        // assign indegree and out degree for each person
        for (int i = 0; i < trust.length; i++) {
            outdegrees[trust[i][0]]++;
            indegrees[trust[i][1]]++;
        }

        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            // town judge must have 0 degrees out, and n-1 degrees in
            if (outdegrees[i] == 0 && indegrees[i] == n-1) {
                return i;
            }
        }
        return -1;
    }
}
```

