# Intuition
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Everybody except the town judge himself trust the town judge. Total number of people is n. So To exist a town judge there has to be a person who is trusted by n-1 people.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(n).
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
/**
 * @param {number} n
 * @param {number[][]} trust
 * @return {number}
 */
var findJudge = function(n, trust) {
    let arr = Array(n+1).fill(0);
    for([i, j] of trust){
        arr[i] -= 1;
