It'll be solved using **directed graph** by counting in & outdegree for all people, then make sure that the judge doesn't have any **outdegree** and have n-1 **indegree**.

For ex: Input: n = 3, trust = [[1, 3], [2, 3]] will be represent by the follwing graph
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/30c7a729-c4e7-4f9b-aad3-04af664001de_1641252032.3218687.png)
Node 3 will have indegree = 2 which equal n-1 '3-1' and outdegree = 0

##### Solution:

```
 public int FindJudge(int n, int[][] trust) {
        int[] indegree = new int[n +1];
        int[] outdegree = new int[n +1];
        int judge = -1;
        foreach(int[] person in trust){
            indegree[person[1]]++;
            outdegree[person[0]]++;
        }

        for(int i=1; i <= n; i++)
            if(indegree[i] == n-1 && outdegree[i] == 0 && judge == -1)
                judge = i;

        return judge;     
    }
